-- Gap E1: literal-free Float arithmetic in an ANNOTATED function.  `double`'s
-- body `x + x` has no Float literal to anchor body-use inference, so the emitter
-- formerly defaulted `x` to LTInt → integer arith on a boxed-Float word →
-- garbage.  The DECLARED `: Float -> Float` now SEEDS the param/return LTy
-- (declSigTypeNames → installDeclSigTypes → inferSigs seed), so `x + x` is FLOAT
-- add and the result is 6.28 == oracle.
double : Float -> Float
double x = x + x

main : <IO> Unit
main = println (floatToString (double 3.14))
